HEADWORD: Uterine
<hw>U"ter*ine</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>uterinus</ets> born of the same mother, from <ets>uterus</ets>
womb: cf. F. <ets>ut⟦eacute⟧rin</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or instrument to the uterus, or womb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Born of the same mother, but by a different
father.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Walter Pope, <qex>uterine</qex> brother to Dr. Joh.
Wilki<?/<?/.</q> <rj><qau>Wood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

